  "text": "where x s k = SoC k , u s k = P b,k , and f s (·) is the model [CITATION_1] . In many studies, V oc and R b , which are functions of SoC, i.e., V oc (t) = V oc SoC(t) and R b (t) = R b SoC(t) , are assumed to be constant [CITATION_2] . Such an assumption reduces the model complexity but also decreases the model fidelity. In this paper, to model the SoC dynamics more accurately, the variations of V oc and R b with SoC are accounted for in the prediction model.",
